{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-js","path":"/posts/life/2020/03/small-rides","webpackCompilationHash":"8d53282eaecc41f6f95f","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Small rides on weekends","description":"It was time for me to go for my first group ride.","date":"March 18th, 2020","categories":["life","biking"],"keywords":["rishabh","rishabh jain","life","rishabh1403","blog","biking"],"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7772511848341233,"src":"/static/716568c816c3ff17aa2f32d01983821d/883ab/small.jpg","srcSet":"/static/716568c816c3ff17aa2f32d01983821d/32ee9/small.jpg 500w,\n/static/716568c816c3ff17aa2f32d01983821d/2f7e7/small.jpg 1000w,\n/static/716568c816c3ff17aa2f32d01983821d/883ab/small.jpg 2000w,\n/static/716568c816c3ff17aa2f32d01983821d/7146c/small.jpg 3000w,\n/static/716568c816c3ff17aa2f32d01983821d/f4afe/small.jpg 4000w,\n/static/716568c816c3ff17aa2f32d01983821d/0b354/small.jpg 6000w","sizes":"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px"},"resize":{"src":"/static/716568c816c3ff17aa2f32d01983821d/93ebb/small.jpg"}}}},"fields":{"readingTime":{"text":"4 min read"}},"html":"<p>It was time for me to go for my first group ride.</p>\n<!--more-->\n<p>I had joined a biking group. It was time to go for a ride. On our first\nbreakfast ride, I was so excited I couldn't sleep the whole night. The plan was to\nleave at 5 am early in the morning. I was sure that we are going to be delayed.\nNo one is punctual in India, especially about things like leaving on time,\ncoming on time and so on. Since I couldn't sleep the whole day, I was at the first\nmeeting spot on time. It took me by surprise to see Kartik and Sankalp there on\ntime too. Wow, people do follow rules here!!!<img class=\"emoji-icon\" alt=\"emoji-laughing\" data-icon=\"emoji-laughing\" style=\"display: inline; margin: 0; margin-top: 1px; position: relative; top: 5px; width: 25px\" src=\"data:image/png;base64, \" title=\"emoji-laughing\">.</p>\n<h1 id=\"the-rules\"><a href=\"#the-rules\" aria-label=\"the rules permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The rules</h1>\n<p>We left on time, and we met more people at the meeting point 2 and 3 and finally, we\nwere heading towards our destination for breakfast. By the way, Kartik left 2 of\nthem behind who weren't on time. This haunts me till now and helps me come on\ntime on every ride.</p>\n<p>The moment we hit the highway, I started to increase my speed only to be stopped\nby another rule, \"No one shall overtake the lead\". I was like, what the heck!!!,\nthe lead(Kartik) was driving at 80kmph, that was slow, but to stick to the\nrules, I stay just on his tails. I thought of a new Idea, I started slowing\ndown, and thought I'll keep myself the last and then will drive fast\novertaking everyone till I reach the lead. But, rule alert!!! \"No one shall ride\nbehind the tail\". I was lost. I was stuck driving at 80kmph the whole way. If\nanyone slowed the whole group slowed, if anyone went fast, well you can't\novertake the lead, so play between the tail and the lead. </p>\n<p>At first, it was frustrating for me, but soon I started realizing the logic and\nimportance of these rules. The whole group sticks together like a team. We were\non a <strong>group ride</strong>, not an individual ride. I realized the importance more\nwhen I took a wrong turn and got lost. Soon, Kartik found me and I saw the whole\ngroup waiting for me. </p>\n<h1 id=\"ride-slow-ride-long\"><a href=\"#ride-slow-ride-long\" aria-label=\"ride slow ride long permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Ride slow, ride long</h1>\n<p>After this ride, we did a lot of smaller rides, and every time I learned a new\nthing about the mechanics of a group ride. I started getting more and more\nconfident on-road and in turn, started enjoying our slow ride. Individually, you\nare fast but vulnerable, in a group you are slow but safe. I always wanted to\nride for my whole life, and Kartik helped me understand that you ride slow,\nyou ride long. The faster you ride above the speed limit, the sooner my biking\ncan end. This stuck by me and stopped trying to overtake him every time. </p>\n<p>Well, although I started following the rules somewhat happy and whole\nheartedly, having a sports bike, sometimes I wanted to unleash all that power.\nWell, thankfully, sometimes Kartik allowed me to overtake him and for the first\ntime, I touched <strong><em>140kmph</em></strong>(I crossed this one later too) on a road with a speed limit of <strong><em>80kmph</em></strong>. I was enjoying my\nsomewhat freedom and laxation of rules responsibly and exploited it only on some\noccasions.</p>\n<p>We went on many short rides ranging from 70kms to 300kms round trip rides for\nbreakfast or lunch depending on the weather. In all of them, the highlight was\nthe ride and not the food. We usually eat the same thing every time with a cup of\ntea/coffee.</p>\n<p>After many short rides, it was time for a long ride. Lansdowne, it was. My first\nlong ride. I'm gonna end this one here and talk about Lansdowne in the next one.</p>\n<p>That's it for this one guys, stay tuned and I'll see you around.</p>"}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"posts/life/2020/03/small-rides","prev":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Lansdowne bike trip","description":"After a long wait, it was time for my first long ride. It wasn't very long to be honest, just 682kms round trip, but for me, this was the longest I've ever ridden a bike. The date we finalized was 9th-10th November'19 and the destination was Lansdowne. It is a nice quiet place in the middle of nowhere on a hilltop. Where there is a hill, we must take bikes. ","categories":["life","travel","biking"],"date":"March 18th, 2020","shortDate":"Mar 18th","year":"2020","path":"posts/life/2020/03/lansdowne-bike-trip","draft":false},"fields":{"readingTime":{"text":"5 min read"}}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Joined a biking group!!!","description":"So I got a new bike, I was over the moon, but I was new to biking. I wanted to take it to all parts of the country, but knew nothing about safety gear or fixing small issues with the bike. I knew what I had to do...join a biking group.","categories":["life","biking"],"date":"March 18th, 2020","shortDate":"Mar 18th","year":"2020","path":"posts/life/2020/03/joined-biking-group","draft":false},"fields":{"readingTime":{"text":"3 min read"}}}}}}